        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">Quinocycle sorts used inventory into grades. Grade A boxes — minimal creasing, no tears, clean interiors — work best for customer-facing takeaway. Lower grades are excellent for back-of-stall storage where appearance matters less than capacity.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Sanitisation for Food-Adjacent Use</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">While used boxes should never contact raw food directly, vendors can line clean Grade A boxes with food-grade parchment or sealed bags to create safe, attractive takeaway containers. This is common practice at long-running bazaars.</p>

        <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-4">Bulk Packs for Full-Month Supply</h3>
        <p class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed mb-6">A typical bazaar stall runs through 200–400 cartons over a full Ramadan month. Quinocycle bulk packs let vendors pre-order 30 days of supply at wholesale rates, delivered to your Balakong or Kajang address before Day One.</p>
      </section>

